
$Id$

A. Supported Decision Diagrams:
-------------------------------

(1) Multi-way Decision Diagrams (MDDs).
(2) Multi-Terminal MDDs (MTMDDs) (real and integer terminal values supported).
(3) Matrix Diagrams (MXDs).
(4) Multi-Terminal MXDs (MTMXDs).
(5) Edge-Valued MDDs (EVMDDs): EV+MDDs, EV*MDDs (only for reals)



B. Operations on Decision Diagrams:
-----------------------------------

Status:
-------
Y: Stable
y: Unstable (untested or known to have bugs or likely to change)
n: Under development (expect to be implemented short-term)
N: Planned (expected to be implemented medium to long-term)
BLANK: No plans.


---------------------------------------------------------------
| Operation     |                  Decision Diagram           |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|               | MDD | MXD | MTMDD | MTMXD | EV+MDD | EV*MDD |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Cardinality   |  Y  |  Y  |   Y   |   Y   |   Y    |   Y    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Node Count    |  Y  |  Y  |   Y   |   Y   |   Y    |   Y    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Edge Count    |  Y  |  Y  |   Y   |   Y   |   Y    |   Y    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Set Complement|  n  |  n  |       |       |        |        |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Set Union     |  Y  |  Y  |       |       |        |        |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Set Intersect |  Y  |  Y  |       |       |        |        |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Set Difference|  Y  |  Y  |       |       |        |        |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Post-Image    |  Y  |  Y  |   Y   |   Y   |   N    |   N    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Pre-Image     |  Y  |  Y  |   Y   |   Y   |   N    |   N    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Breadth-First |  Y  |  Y  |   n   |   n   |   N    |   N    |
| Reachability  |     |     |       |       |        |        |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Depth-First   |  Y  |  Y  |   n   |   n   |   N    |   N    |
| Reachability  |     |     |       |       |        |        |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|               | MDD | MXD | MTMDD | MTMXD | EV+MDD | EV*MDD |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| *             |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   Y    |   Y    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| +             |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   Y    |   Y    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| -             |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   Y    |   Y    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| /             |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| <             |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| <=            |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| >             |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| <=            |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| ==            |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| !=            |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|               | MDD | MXD | MTMDD | MTMXD | EV+MDD | EV*MDD |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| MIN           |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| MAX           |     |     |   Y   |   Y   |   n    |   n    |
---------------------------------------------------------------


Conversion Operations:
----------------------

Stable:
* MTMDD to MDD and vice-versa.
* MTMXD to MXD and vice-versa.
* MDD to EV+MDD (index sets).

Unstable:
* MTMDD to EV+MDD (false in MTMDD becomes 0 in EV+MDD and true becomes 1).

Short-term:

Long-term:


Other Operations:
-----------------

Stable:
* Batch additions (createEdge()): MDD, EV+MDD, EV*MDD, MXD, MTMXD.
* DD iterators (one element at a time): MDD, MTMDD, EV*MDD, EV+MDD, MXD, MTMXD.

Unstable:

Short-term:
* Batch additions (createEdge()): MTMDD.

Long-term:

C. Current limits of MEDDLY:
-----------------------------------

Maximum number of non-terminal nodes in a forest: 2^31 -1
    why: 
    32-bit signed integers are used numerous places to represent 
    non-terminal nodes.  If we increase this to 64-bit, the
    memory requirements for every node will double.



